title.narrative: Sustaining and Scaling up the Effective HIV/AIDS Prevention, Treatment and Care in Georgia

description.narrative: Georgia - HIV - National Center For Disease Control and Public Health - NCDC. This program has the following goals: To turn the HIV epidemic in the reversal phase through strengthened interventions targeting key affected populations (KAP), and significant improvement in health outcomes for PLHIV.. The objectives of this program are: Improve HIV health outcomes through ensuring universal access to quality treatment, care and support.. Ensure sustainable strong response to the epidemic through enhanced government committment, enabling legislative and operational environment, and greater involvement of civil society. Improve the effectiveness of outreach and prevention and ensure timely detection of HIV and progression to care
